name: Bushfires Victoria
summary: Western Victoria is experiencing bushfires, with one home already lost. Residents in several towns have been ordered to evacuate due to the rapidly spreading fires. Severe thunderstorms and flash flooding are also predicted for eastern Victoria. Emergency and watch-and-act warnings have been issued across the western region. Hundreds of residents have been advised to leave their homes as the fires continue to rage out of control. Authorities have urged residents to evacuate immediately, as the fire poses a significant threat to life and property. The fires have already caused damage to property and livestock in the Great Ocean Road, Otway Ranges, and Wimmera region.

Trump has also announced plans to create a new National Energy Council and appoint Burgum as its leader. This move has drawn criticism from some Democrats who argue that it will give too much power to the fossil fuel industry.
